  , issueCommentBody =
      "Treating 60 seconds as 1 past 59 seconds just means that the string containing \"23:59:60.123\" gets converted to the same time value as \"00:00:00.123\" on the next day.  The epoch_time field of the datetime representation just counts seconds since the epoch, with each year containing either `365 * 24 * 60 * 60` seconds or `366 * 24 * 60 * 60` seconds."
